          input name="m" type="hidden" value="1011294725031"
          input name="p" type="hidden" value="oi"
  section.reasons
    .reasons-inner.bound
      h2 Why LAUP?
      ul.reasons-list
        li.book: p Children enrolled in LAUP programs exceed predetermined literacy and math goals from fall to spring semesters.
        li.attention: p 99% of LAUP children exhibited a high level of attention required for success in kindergarten as opposed to the national average of 84%.
        li.alphabet: p After a year of quality preschool, children in an LAUP program improved from identifying 12 letters of the alphabet to identifying 18, while the national standard is 10 letters.
        li.lightbulb: p After a year of quality preschool, children in LAUP programs surpassed the national average in math skills by approximately two points.
  section.about
    img src="images/laup-img-girl.jpg"
    .about-inner
      .bound
        h2 About LAUP
        p Los Angeles Universal Preschool (LAUP) is a non-profit organization whose mission is to provide access to quality preschool education for children in Los Angeles County. We believe all children deserve the best start in life, and a quality preschool education provides them with a solid foundation for success.
